Name:           @PACKAGE@
Version:        @VERSION@
Release:        1%{?dist}
Summary:        SDL-based image viewer for X and console

License:        GPL-2.0-or-later
URL:            https://www.elfga.com/~erik/
Source0:        https://www.elfga.com/~erik/files/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  gcc
BuildRequires:  make
BuildRequires:  pkgconfig
BuildRequires:  pkgconfig(sdl2)
BuildRequires:  pkgconfig(SDL2_image)
BuildRequires:  openssl-devel
# Runtime library dependencies (libSDL2, libSDL2_image, libssl, libcrypto)
# are picked up automatically from the linked ELF; do not list them here.

%description
Image viewer based on SDL that reads and displays a wide variety of formats.
Features include fullscreen and windowed modes, arbitrary pan and zoom,
slideshow, an on-screen filename display, navigation through a list of
images, operation in both X and the console, and fetching images over
http and (when built with OpenSSL) https, with redirect following.

%prep
%setup -q

%build
%configure
%make_build

%install
%make_install

%files
%license COPYING
%doc README ChangeLog NEWS AUTHORS
%{_bindir}/vp
%{_mandir}/man1/vp.1*

%changelog
* Sun Jul 19 2026 Erik Greenwald <erik@elfga.com> - 1.9-1
- SDL2 port and CMake build alongside autotools
- Optional https support via OpenSSL (certificate verification, -k), IPv6,
  HTTP redirect following, correct HTTP/1.1 framing, -K to keep downloads
- Arbitrary pan/zoom, on-screen filename display, oversized-image handling
- Security hardening of the download path; dropped unimplemented FTP
- See the bundled ChangeLog for the full list
